wiki.content: “EVIL J0RDAN” embraces the deep-voiced theme of Music, as Playboi Carti paints a picture of his mysterious lifestyle. On December 8, 2023, Carti took to Instagram to share two snippets of “EVILJ0RDAN” on his story. The first snippet teased the song’s instrumental with an image designed by SEX IS DEATH that read: "I'M NOT PLAYING" This was followed by another snippet posted two hours later featuring vocals from Carti as well as narration by South Carolina disk jockey, DJ Swamp Izzo. It was teased with the text “2024,” confirming Music’s release year. Carti’s cousin Kee revealed in a tweet that the song had been recorded the previous night, saying "he just made this last night btw" Weeks later, on January 15, 2024, Blackhaine announced the 9:30 PM Eastern Standard Time release for that day, similar to most of the latest singles. The track soon released to Playboi Carti’s alternative Instagram through a music video. Read more on Last.fm.
